headline: Harrow Stock Eyes Relative Strength Rating Upgrade
summary: Harrow stock saw a positive improvement to its Relative Strength (RS) Rating on Thursday, rising from 64 to 79.  IBD's unique RS Rating identifies technical performance by using a 1 (worst) to 99 (best) score that indicates how a stock's price performance over the trailing 52 weeks compares to other publicly traded companies.  See if Harrow stock can continue to rebound and clear that threshold.
